import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='num_dependencies', kde=False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of number of dependencies?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='target', y='num_dependencies', data=data, estimator=max)
    ax.axhline(y=max(data['num_dependencies']), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {max(data['num_dependencies']):.2f}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xlabel('Target Software Package')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Dependencies')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Which software package has the highest number of dependencies?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
